#Text=THE CHURCH.
#Text=Oxford, March s.
#Text=—On Friday last Mr.
#Text=Francis Dyson was elected to the Frost Scholarship, and Mr.
#Text=Thomas Meyrick to the Wiltshire Scholarship at Corpus Christi College.
#Text=This day the following degrees were conferred Doctors in Civil Law—Edwin Maddy, Esq., Brasennose College, Judge of the Consistory Court in the diocese of Gloucester, Grand Compounder; Rev.
#Text=James Duke Coleridge, Ballioi College, Prebendary of Exeter. _ Cambridge, March 3.
#Text=—William Alexander Osborne, scholar of Trinity College, has been elected University Scholar on the Craven foundation.
#Text=—The Pitt scholarship has not yet been filled up. ihe examination for two Scholars on Dr.
#Text=Bells foundation (the Candidates for wkich must be in their first year of admission) and the sons of orphans of Clergymen began this morning, and will continue throughout the week.
#Text=The admirers of learning and true genius, and every friend of tbe Church, will be gratified to hear that the Chancellor has conferred the living of St.
#Text=Stephens.
#Text=Walbrook, upon the Rev.
#Text=George Croly, L.L.D., tbe Author of the work upon the Apocalypse and upon the Cycles of Revelation, as well as one of the most distinguished poets of our generation.
#Text=This is another step in practical Church Reform.
#Text=Irish Church.
#Text=—The Second Report of the Commissioners of Inquiry into Ecclesiastical Revenues and Patronage in Ireland, addressed by the Commissioners to his Majesty, hat recently been printed.
#Text=This report is coufined to Revenue and Patronage under three heais:—l.
#Text=Of all Collegiate and Cathedral Churches, and of all other ecclesiastical corporations connected therewith, such as minor canoories. vicars choralslups, &c. t.
#Text=Of all dignitaries, such as Deans, Precentors, Chancellors, Treasurers, Archdeacons, Provosts, &c.
#Text=S.
